In a #medium pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a 
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. 
Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready 
to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves 
and stems. Zest and halve @lime{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce} over a #small 
bowl{}, reserving juice. In a #medium bowl{}, toss together 
@shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, cilantro, pineapple, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, 
juice from half the lime, half the pineapple juice, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Season 
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @cashews{1%ounce}.

To bowl with reserved pineapple juice, stir in @apricot jam{6%tablespoon}, a 
squeeze of lime juice, and @sriracha{2%teaspoon} to taste. Set aside. Heat a 
#large heavy-bottomed pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium heat. Add 
@shredded coconut{1/4%cup} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until 
lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a second #small 
bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat very dry with #paper towels{}. 
Season with @salt{}. In a #large bowl{}, combine @tempura mix{82%g}, half the 
toasted coconut, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and @cold water{1/3%cup}.

> 2¼ cups water and 2 tsp salt for 4 servings.

Heat a ¼-inch-layer of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for coconut over medium-high 
heat. Stir shrimp into batter until fully coated. Line a #plate{} with paper 
towels.

Once oil is hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the pan, add 
coated shrimp in a single layer. Cook in batches until golden brown and cooked 
through, ~{2-3%minutes} on the first side and ~{1-2%minutes} on the second side.

> Add more oil as needed between batches, allowing it time to heat back up 
> before frying more shrimp.

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer shrimp to paper-towel-lined plate. Immediately 
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest to 
taste; season with @salt{}. Divide rice, shrimp, and tropical slaw between 
plates. Sprinkle shrimp and rice with remaining toasted coconut. Drizzle shrimp 
with sauce (or serve on the side for dipping).